   <item>
      <title>Avandra's Boon of Storms</title>
      <category>Rare</category>
      <fluff>Like an ocean storm, change is both inevitable and rarely controllable, but to those who embrace change rather than fight it, Avandra occasionally grants the power to influence events</fluff>
      <level>
         <value>1</value>
         <price>360</price>
      </level>
      <level>
         <value>11</value>
         <price>9,000</price>
      </level>
      <level>
         <value>21</value>
         <price>225,000</price>
      </level>
      <type>Divine Boon</type>
      <block>
         <name>Property</name>
         <line>You gain a +1 item bonus to Diplomacy checks.</line>
         <line indent="1"><![CDATA[<i>Level 11:</i>]]> +3 item bonus.</line>
         <line indent="1"><![CDATA[<i>Level 21:</i>]]> +5 item bonus.</line>
      </block>
      <block>
         <name>Utility Power</name>
         <frequency>Daily</frequency>
         <action>Nonaction</action> <subaction>Interrupt</subaction>
         <line><![CDATA[<i>Trigger:</i>]]> You make a skill check and don't like the result</line>
         <line><![CDATA[<i>Effect:</i>]]> You reroll the skill check and use the second result, even if it's lower.</line>
         <line indent="1"><![CDATA[<i>Level 11:</i>]]> Use whichever result is higher.</line>
         <line indent="1"><![CDATA[<i>Level 21:</i>]]> If the triggering skill check still fails, you regain the use of this power when you take a short rest.</line>
      </block>
   </item>
   
   <item>
      <title>Bahamut's Protective Ward</title>
      <category>Rare</category>
      <fluff>Bahamut grants his boon to heroes who shield the weak from the strong, and individuals who fight in Bahamut's name are beacons of hope and protection</fluff>
      <level>
         <value>3</value>
         <price>680</price>
      </level>
      <level>
         <value>8</value>
         <price>3,400</price>
      </level>
      <level>
         <value>13</value>
         <price>17,000</price>
      </level>
      <level>
         <value>18</value>
         <price>85,000</price>
      </level>
      <level>
         <value>23</value>
         <price>425,000</price>
      </level>
      <level>
         <value>28</value>
         <price>2,125,000</price>
      </level>
      <type>Divine Boon</type>
      <block>
         <name>Property</name>
         <line>You gain a +1 item bonus to attack rolls with <![CDATA[<i>opportunity attacks</i>]]>.</line>
         <line indent="1"><![CDATA[<i>Level 13 or 18:</i>]]> +2 item bonus.</line>
         <line indent="1"><![CDATA[<i>Level 23 or 28:</i>]]> +3 item bonus.</line>
      </block>
      <block>
         <name>Attack Power</name>
         <frequency>Daily</frequency>
         <action>Minor</action> <subaction>Action</subaction>
         <line><![CDATA[<i>Effect:</i>]]> Until the end of your next turn, enemies provoke <![CDATA[<i>opportunity attacks</i>]]> from you if they make an attack that does not include as a target.</line>
         <line indent="1"><![CDATA[<i>Level 8 or 13:</i>]]> You gain a +1 bonus to these attacks.</line>
         <line indent="1"><![CDATA[<i>Level 18, 23, or 28:</i>]]> You gain a +2 bonus to these attacks.</line>
      </block>
